  PACKAGES :- 
   ===========  

   => a package is a collection of procedures & functions 
   => related procedures & functions can be grouped into one program called package.
   
   
     SERVER
            DATABASE
                       USER
                                   PROCEDURES  (standalone procedures)
                                   FUNCTIONS       (standalone functions)
                                   PACKAGE
                                           PROCEDURES
                                           FUNCTIONS

 Advantages :- 
 --------------------
   
  1  easy to manage :- 
    ---------------------------
  
    => because related procedures & functions available in single package , so manaing is easy

2   supports overloading :-
     ------------------------------

   => standalone proc / func doesn't support overloading but package supports overloading 
         i.e. in package we can define two or more proc / func with same name and 
         with different parameters.

3  supports hiding :- 
     ------------------------

  => standalone proc & func are public i.e they can be invoked from any where but in package
       we can declare proc / func public and private , public members can be called from 
        any where but private members can be called within package.

 4   improves performance :-
     --------------------------------------

  => when application program calls a proc/func in a package then oracle not only loads 
       requested member but entire package loaded into memory and  next request will not got to
      db and reduces no of requests going to db and improves performance.

 


